<p>You can also put regular text between your rows of images. Say you wanted to write a little bit about your project before you posted the rest of the images. You describe how you toiled, sweated, <em>bled</em> for your project, and thenâ€¦. you reveal itâ€™s glory in the next row of images.</p>

<div class="img_row">
	<img class="col two" src="/img/6.jpg" alt="" title="example image" />
	<img class="col one" src="/img/11.jpg" alt="" title="example image" />
</div>
<div class="col three caption">
	You can also have artistically styled 2/3 + 1/3 images, like these.
</div>

<p><br /><br /><br /></p>

<p>The code is simple. Just add a col class to your image, and another class specifying the width: one, two, or three columns wide. Hereâ€™s the code for the last row of images above:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>&lt;div class="img_row"&gt;
  &lt;img class="col two" src="/img/6.jpg"/&gt;
  &lt;img class="col one" src="/img/11.jpg"/&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</code></pre></div></div>
